{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "vop", "internal": "shinymetal", "icon": "VOP/shinymetal", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Shiny Metal"], "extent": [71, 87]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Simulates a shiny metallic material with strong reflective\nproperties."], "extent": [87, 166]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This operator simulates a shiny metallic material with strong reflective\nproperties."], "extent": [166, 252]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The default parameters of this operator yield a gold material. Other\nparameter configurations you might find useful are listed below:"], "extent": [252, 387]}, {"lang": null, "type": "pre", "indent": 0, "text": ["\nMaterial                   color      diffamp specamp reflamp urough\nvrough\n---------------------+---------------+-------+-------+-------+------+------\n        Polished Gold          0.97,0.88,0.30   .2      3.0     .8    \n.20    .20\n        Polished Silver        0.75,0.75,0.75   .2      2.5     .8    \n.17    .17\n        Chrome                 0.95,0.95,0.95   .3      3.25    .95   \n.12    .12\n        Rolled Brass           0.92,0.57,0.05   .1      3.3     .7    \n.05    .16\n        Rolled Aluminum        0.90,0.88,0.85   .1      2.1     .7    \n.04    .09\n        Brushed Aluminum       0.90,0.88,0.85   .15     1.9     .55   \n.088   .13\n        Anodized Red Aluminum  0.90,0.35,0.35   .15     1.9     .55   \n.088   .13\n        Anodized Blue Aluminum 0.30,0.55,0.70   .15     1.9     .55   \n.088   .13\n"], "extent": [387, 1203]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The simulated metal will reflect both its environment and the optional\nreflection map. Leave the reflection map field empty to avoid map\nreflections. For a simpler metal model, see ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/chromenv", "type": "link", "text": ["Chrome Environment"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/chromenv"}, "."], "extent": [1203, 1425]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This operator uses Anisotropic Specular as the lighting model, which is\nill suited for non-subdivided polygonal geometry. See the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/lighting", "type": "link", "text": ["Lighting Model"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/lighting"}, "\noperator for more details."], "extent": [1425, 1618]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["If the Position (", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, ") input and the Normal (", {"type": "code", "text": ["N"]}, ") input are not connected,\nthe global variables by the same names will be used instead. Typically\nyou will use ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/restpos", "type": "link", "text": ["Rest Position"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/restpos"}, " or ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg", "type": "link", "text": ["UV Space Change"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg"}, " as inputs for ", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, ", and\nwill not touch ", {"type": "code", "text": ["N"]}, " unless you want to apply additional displacement to\nthe metal surface using an operator such as ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise", "type": "link", "text": ["Bump Noise"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise"}, ". If you need to\naccess the global variables directly, they are available from the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/global", "type": "link", "text": ["Global Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global"}, " operator."], "extent": [1618, 2150]}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [2150, 2159], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise"}], "extent": [2159, 2186]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/chromenv", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/chromenv"}], "extent": [2186, 2212]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/global", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global"}], "extent": [2212, 2236]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/lighting", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/lighting"}], "extent": [2236, 2262]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/rust", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/rust"}], "extent": [2262, 2285]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Shiny Metal"], "summary": ["Simulates a shiny metallic material with strong reflective\nproperties."]}